credit.credit-words: "All should take time for the daily study of the word of God, with earnest prayer that they may learn the way of life and salvation."
And the assurance is, ‘I will instruct thee and teach thee in the way which thou shalt go:
All should realize their entire dependence upon God. ‘Looking unto Jesus' is ever to be our motto.
". They seek me daily, and delight to know my ways, as a nation that did righteousness,
The voice of prayer and the melody of holy song should ascend as sweet incense.
I will guide thee with mine eye' (Psalm 32:8)."
and forsook not the ordinance of their God: they ask of me the ordinances of justice;
they take delight in approaching to God."
". Take time to ask counsel of Him [God].
